               <head>Sefer ha-yesodot by Euclid</head>
               
               
               
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh2008107563" rend="visible">
                  
                  
                  
                  <summary>An mathematical treatise. </summary>
                  
                  
                  
                  <textLang mainLang="he"/>
                  
                  
                  
                  <msItem rend="">
                     
                     
                     
                     <locus from="1v" to="177v"/>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer ha-yesodot </title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">ספר היסודות </title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <author>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="en" key="viaf.org/viaf/176184097">Euclid </persName>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="he" key="viaf.org/viaf/176184097">אוקלידס</persName>
                     
                     
                     
                     </author>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The thirteen Books of the Elements of Euclid, with the addition of two Books at the end which are ascribed to Hypsikles. The Hebrew translator was Moses ben Samuel ibn Tibbon. Figures throughout the manuscript. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Book ii begins on folio 15v; book iii, folio 23r; book iv, folio 35r; book v, folio 41v; book vi, folio 51v; book vii, folio 64r; book viii, folio 70v; book ix, folio folio 80v; book x, folio 89r; book xi, folio 135v; book xii, folio 151r; book, folio xiii, folio 160v. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Folio 177v gives a list of fifteen books with the number of figures belonging to each, the entire number being stated to be 466. The Numbers of the figures are also stated in later writing at the end of the different books. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Folios 101-102 contain a fragment of a work on arithmetic (in a later Ashkenazi script). </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Author, <persName xml:lang="he" key="viaf.org/viaf/64172358">Moses ibn Tibbon</persName>'s colophon on folio 177r.</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Latin inscription on folio 1r suggesting erroneously that the MS was written by the translator Moses ibn Tibbon in 1270 (see author's colophon).</p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                  
                  
                  
                  </msItem>
               
               
               
               </msContents>
               
               
               
